Our 1895 home is very near the T (Orange line) and many cool Jamaica Plain spots. Sorry, no breakfast and no late arrivals. We are engaged in a green renovation of an historical home -- stained glass and solar panels -- and, of course, insulation -- lots of it. In addition to a ceiling and box fan, there is now also air conditioning.  The room is spacious and includes a desk and chair. The room is on the third floor of a Victorian -- so lots of stairs, but we can help with luggage. The bathroom is on the second floor. Room and shared bath only. Sorry, no kitchen access nor refrigerator space. However, while you should generally leave with what you came with, we're happy to help with your trash and recycling.
